  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which devour widows' houses,.... As the characters of them, in the preceding verse, expose their pride, this shows their avarice; they were very voracious and cruel; they did not spare widows, but devoured their substance: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and for a show make long prayers; to cover their wickedness, pretending great devotion and religion; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the same shall receive greater damnation: than openly profane sinners; doing such wickedness under a cloak of religion, will aggravate their condemnation; See Gill on Matthew 23:14. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "the same shall receive greater damnation: than openly profane sinners; doing such wickedness under a cloak of religion, will aggravate their condemnation; See Gill on ",
