        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for a shew",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "in pretence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Their hypocrisy was so notorious that even the Talmud records the warning given by Alexander Jannaeus to his wife on his deathbed against ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "painted",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Pharisees. And in their seven classes of Pharisees the Talmudic writers place “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Shechemites",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "”— Pharisees from self-interest; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Stumblers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—so mock-humble that they will not raise their feet from the ground; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Bleeders—so",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " mock-modest, that because they will not raise their eyes, they run against walls, &c. Thus the Jewish writers themselves depict the Pharisees as the Tartuffes of antiquity.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
