        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "damnation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Rather, judgment. The word is not even ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "katakrima",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or ‘condemnation.’ Their ‘judgment’ shall be more severe than that of those who practised ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "none",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of these religious ordinances. It should be “more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the judgment” than for these, ",
